It's time to demolish our bedroom. The last room in the house that hasn't been touched except for a little decorating.
The disgusting electric fireplace and the fireplace base have to go. We need to build a fireplace, replace the cracked plaster, and smooth it out. Then build a custom closet.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch…
The dirty part of the work is done.
We found a few dead birds in the chimney, very dry :(
Everything is ready for the stucco artist next week
The small side niche turned out nicely
A new wardrobe is coming in here (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we even thought about installing this nice little vent flap, so the chimney doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and the cap. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest there🪺
The plasterer is done. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlay is in place, I made a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Floor parts are ready and can be laid. We are currently having tea break
Buhu. Today progress is slow due to super complicated cuts around the door posts, so we can have a smooth transition to the corridor (where the floor will also be laid). @user45@twitter.com has cursed me
Finished, but at the end! The crown was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. We will sleep well tonight!
The floor in the hallway and all baseboards are still missing. The decorator comes in a month, so we currently have raw plaster style
A little more DIY work in the evening, to cut or chisel out the lower sections around the door posts, so that the floor will fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlay is now also in the hallway.
Yesterday we finished the floor in the hallway! Then at 5 a.m. we left to pick up item 1 at Heathrow, then a little nap and final push in the hallway, the boards are installed. The joints will be made once the glue is dry
